{"version":"0.1.0","asset":{"Parent":{"$content":"xenonauts-:-GC-::-masters/item/shield.json","$t":"ar_Template"},"_components":[{"$content":"","$t":"GCItemMeta"},{"$content":"Shields are protective items held in the Primary slot that can absorb incoming damage. Unlike shields in the original Xenonauts 2, shields in Unification War behave like {{_context.tooltips.concept  filename:\"armour\" text:\"armour\"}}, making them harder to destroy but subject to {{_context.tooltips.concept filename:\"armour_penetration\" text:\"Armour Penetration\"}}.\n\nShields have a 100% chance of blocking any projectile, melee attack, or explosion striking the soldier in the forward 90-degree arc, but the protection offered at the sides declines linearly until it reaches 20% at the edges of the frontal 180-degree arc. No protection is offered to the rear,  against weapons dealing gas damage, or against environmental effects such as smoke, fire, or corrosive gas.\n\nSoldiers can use a one-handed weapon in their Secondary slot while using a shield. Pistols or melee weapons are a good choice.\n\nAny damage absorbed by a shield will reduce its Armour, and the shield is destroyed when this reaches 0.","$t":"Description"},{"$content":[{"Prerequisite":{"Forward":"Slot","Delegate":{"Operator":"Any","Number":0,"Children":[{"Target":"Xenonauts.Common.Components.Item.CombatantSlots","Compare":"Overlaps","Value":{"$content":"Belt,Backpack","$t":"CombatantSlots"},"UseInventoryType":true,"Variant":"Unlocks","modifierStorage":null,"$t":"DLEPq"},{"Operator":"All","Number":0,"selector":{"OneComponent":"Xenonauts.Common.Components.Item.InventorySlotOwnerLink","$t":"OneEntitySe"},"prerequisites":[{"Operator":"None","Number":0,"Children":[{"Operator":"Any","Number":0,"selector":{"ManyComponent":"Xenonauts.Common.Components.Item.InventorySlotsLink","$t":"ManyEntitySe"},"prerequisite":{"Operator":"All","Number":0,"Children":[{"Target":"Xenonauts.Common.Components.Item.CombatantSlots","Compare":"Is","Value":{